╭─ Assistant [MainThread@22430] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ An incorrect transformation in `instcombine` simplifies a `select` instruction involving an `icmp samesign` instruction, leading to a miscompilation. The `samesign` keyword can cause   │
│ an `icmp` to produce `poison` if the operands have different signs. The optimization logic in `foldAndOrOfICmpsWithConstEq` does not account for this poison-producing behavior.         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformation incorrectly assumes that if `X samesign_eq C` is true, then `X` must be equal to `C`. This assumption is flawed because if `X` and `C` have different signs, the      │
│ comparison yields `poison`, not `false`. The optimization then proceeds to incorrectly simplify other comparisons based on this flawed assumption, leading to `poison` being returned    │
│ where a concrete value is expected.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to prevent `foldAndOrOfICmpsWithConstEq` from running when the equality comparison has the `samesign` keyword. This is achieved by adding a check at the beginning of the     │
│ function to bail out if `Cmp0->hasSameSign()` is true.                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```patch                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp                                                                                                                            │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp                                                                                                                            │
│ @@ -1265,6 +1265,11 @@                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                            bool IsAnd, bool IsLogical,                                                                                                                   │
│                                            InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder,                                                                                                             │
│                                            const SimplifyQuery &Q) {                                                                                                                     │
│ +  // The logic below doesn't account for the poison semantics of 'samesign'.                                                                                                            │
│ +  // It assumes that if `X == C` is true, then `X` is `C`. But with `samesign`,                                                                                                         │
│ +  // `X == C` can be poison, which is not handled.                                                                                                                                      │
│ +  if (Cmp0->hasSameSign())                                                                                                                                                              │
│ +    return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                     │
│    // Match an equality compare with a non-poison constant as Cmp0.                                                                                                                      │
│    // Also, give up if the compare can be constant-folded to avoid looping.                                                                                                              │
│    ICmpInst::Predicate Pred0;                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
